      "content": "It's hard to disagree with you. Everything feels so pointless. I look at the doctors and the pills and the way everyone treats me like I'm already gone, and I just... I feel like I've lost all my agency. I'm just watching my life slip away, sitting in this chair, waiting for my body to just give out on its own. It feels so passive, like I'm just a passenger in my own decline.",
